# Plan Mode Feature Documents

- When Plan Mode is used, save the final approved plan in `proto/features/{index}-{date}-{feature}.md`.
- Use a zero-padded sequential `{index}` if existing feature documents already use one; otherwise use the next plain integer.
- Use `{date}` in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
- Use a short lowercase kebab-case `{feature}` name that describes the work.
- Write saved feature documents in English because they are repository content.
- If the chat plan was created in another language, translate it to English before saving it under `proto/features/`.
- Keep file paths, identifiers, and code references unchanged during translation.
- Preserve the approved plan completely when saving it: include the overview, all to-dos and their statuses, every section heading, Context, Plan, Notes, schemas, Mermaid diagrams, code snippets, references, assumptions, verification steps, and any other content from the plan.
- Do not summarize, collapse, reorder, or omit plan content. Translate prose to English when required, but keep the original structure, section coverage, list items, diagrams, and technical details intact.
